where me is the mass pr. unit length (the added mass is included for transverse translations, but neglected for rotational and longitudinal degrees of freedom). The added mass coefficient (Ca) for a circular cylinder can be found analytically and is exactly 1 (for non-oscillating flow). The factor α should ideally be negative or zero since the trans
